To check status of docker daemon and other docker services:
	$ docker info

To initialize docker swarm:
	$ docker swarm init

	OR

	$ docker swarm init --advertise-addr 192.168.33.10 --listen-addr 192.168.33.10   # If there are multiple network interface, take IP of one interface and initilize the docker swarm

	$ docker node ls 	# To check node list


To create docker swarm token:
	$ docker swarm join-token manager		# To add node as a manger

	$ docker swarm join-token worker 		# To add node as a worker

	Output will be like this: 
		$ docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-2ifizwg4fy764og6qiq40inp4taluvbmdjs9enkmabidb8epwn-cofkptdagznmuv3hri2grkpdy 192.168.33.10:2377

Note: a.  If there is any certification issue, Please refer the following link to resolve it. 
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45502822/docker-swarm-error-response-from-daemon-error-while-validating-root-ca-certifi
	  b. If there is port or firewall issue, execute the following commands
	  sudo firewall-cmd --zone=public --add-port=2377/tcp --permanent
	  sudo firewall-cmd --reload
